comments.body:
Using a ternary here feels more appropiate, also, as mentioned several times already we should keep using the `Array<T>` notation for consistency.

```suggestion
const getPickedEditHandles = (picks?: Array<Pick> | null): Array<EditHandleFeature> => {
  const handles = picks
    ? picks
        .filter((pick) => pick.isGuide && pick.object.properties.guideType === 'editHandle')
        .map((pick) => pick.object)
    : [];

  return handles;
};
```

