comments.body:
I'm starting to see a pattern with the whole `currentActiveTab === [number]`, it works but we are tying ourselves too much into a specific order that could be hard to change, maybe making it clear by using the name trough a const would be clearer. And as always feel free to tell me this is trash.

```javascript
const ROUTE_DETAILS = 'Route Details'
const SPREADS = 'Spreads'
const LAYDOWNS = 'Laydowns'

const tabs = [
  { id: 0, name: ROUTE_DETAILS },
  { id: 1, name: SPREADS},
  { id: 2, name: LAYDOWNS}
]

const isActiveTab = (current, id) => current === id
const getActiveTab = (current) => tabs.find(({ id }) => isActiveTab(current, id))
```

```suggestion
      <div className="flex justify-between text-sm">
        {tabs.map({ id, name }) => (
            <Tab selected={isActiveTab(id)} onClick={() => handleTabClick(id)}>
              {name}
            </Tab>
          )}
      </div>
      <div className="w-80 h-full">
        <div className="flex flex-col h-full">
          {getActiveTab(currentActiveTab) === ROUTE_DETAILS && <RouteDetails {...props} />}
          {getActiveTab(currentActiveTab) === SPREADS && <Spreads {...props} />}
          {getActiveTab(currentActiveTab) === LAYDOWNS && <div>Laydowns</div>}
        </div>
      </div>      
```

