The idea is ~~trash~~ great. I like having Tabs stored as a const somewhere and then mapping that. I'm not sure about the `id` though, it feels like it's being used in a similar way as an `index`.

```
{tabs.map(_, index) => (
  <Tab selected={isActiveTab(index)} onClick={() => handleTabClick(index)}>
    {name}
  </Tab>
)}
```

And because we keep track of this value in Redux, when rendering the actual component we could so something like: `currentActiveTab === RoutePlannerTabs.ROUTE_DETAILS && <RouteDetails {...props} />`

