The idea behind iterating inside JSX is to keep it as DRY as possible. Even though this is good as we're avoiding calling the `<Tab>` component thrice, we're still repeating ourselves by declaring the array inline.

If you agree with the change above, we can then do:

```
  Object.values(RoutePlannerSidebarTab).map((tab) => (
    <Tab key={tab} selected={currentActiveTab === tab} onClick={() => handleTabClick(tab)}>
      {tab}
    </Tab>
  ));
```

