@msallent I disagree that this bug was introduced in the manual modification branch. As I mentioned in your [Segments Implementation](https://github.com/iMercatus/imercata-web/pull/280#issuecomment-905763640), the line issue still showed up there (albeit, maybe infrequently). 

To check that this bug existed before the manual modification, I downloaded the state of the app from your deleted [Segments Implementation branch](https://github.com/iMercatus/imercata-web/tree/28376447cdf77c9c4f9f481ec3da2fccd02f4542) and repeated the process of adding points and then rapidly clicking undo/redo. It appears that the lines were still not being drawn consistently in that branch, too. When this issue occurs, the lines ONLY redraw when interacting with the map (ie zooming, dragging, etc.), which leads me to believe the state of the map needs to be updated (ie `setViewPort` or perhaps delete the `onViewStateChange` and allow deck.gl to figure out state changes). See video below:


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30512292/131534372-568e86b5-464a-4801-bf05-f72e49315f0b.mov

